Oppenheimer Industries Inc said itexpects to report a loss for the year ended January 31 of about980,000 dlrs, compared with a profit of 211,074 dlrs a yearbefore.    The company blamed the loss on the continuing depression inagriculture, the discontinuance of several programs due to thepassage if the 1986 tax bill and the failure to close the saleof four ranches in the California Carrizo Plains during theyear as expected.    The company said the prospective purchaser forfieted a500,000 dlr deposit  It said it is in talks on a new contract. Reuter&#3;